pool.baseline:
I'm working on an embedded C++ project for an automotive ECU and we're seeing a slow memory leak. It's not crashing immediately, but the heap is slowly exhausting over a 4-hour period. 

Here is a simplified version of the telemetry processing loop where we suspect the issue is:

```cpp
void process_sensor_data(const SensorPacket* packet) {
    if (packet->status == VALID) {
        DataBuffer* buffer = new DataBuffer(packet->payload_size);
        buffer->copy_from(packet->payload);

        // Add to the processing queue
        m_queue.push_back(buffer);
    }

    // Update metrics
    m_metrics.total_packets_processed++;
}

void maintenance_cycle() {
    // Periodically try to clear old data
    auto it = m_queue.begin();
    while (it != m_queue.end()) {
        if ((*it)->is_expired()) {
            // System should free memory here
            it = m_queue.erase(it);
        } else {
            ++it;
        }
    }
}
```

Can you give me a systematic way to debug this? I can't use heavy tools like Valgrind on the actual hardware due to resource constraints.

